<Row>
<Cell ss:StyleID="Text"><Data ss:Type="String">Nutrition and Dietetics</Data></Cell>
<Cell ss:StyleID="Text"><Data ss:Type="String">4</Data></Cell>
<Cell ss:StyleID="Text"><Data ss:Type="String">BES 124</Data></Cell>
<Cell ss:StyleID="Text"><Data ss:Type="String">Nutritional Anthropology</Data></Cell>
<Cell ss:StyleID="Text"><Data ss:Type="String">2</Data></Cell>
<Cell ss:StyleID="Text"><Data ss:Type="String">2+0+0</Data></Cell>
<Cell ss:StyleID="Text"><Data ss:Type="String">2</Data></Cell>
<Cell ss:StyleID="Text"><Data ss:Type="String">3</Data></Cell>
<Cell ss:StyleID="Text"><Data ss:Type="String">24.02.2026</Data></Cell>
<Cell ss:StyleID="Text"><Data ss:Type="String">The theoretical scope of the course is the basis of the vocational courses, professional practices and the branches of science supporting this field in the field of Nutrition and Dietetics in the third and fourth grades. The course contributes to the acquisition of evidence-based information, the use of research skills and the planning of scientific research, the integration of theoretical and applied knowledge of the field and outside the field. It contributes to the acquisition of the knowledge, skills and competencies required for the planning of the nutritional care process and its implementation within the framework of ethical principles. The course will be conducted remotely. It will be carried out with synchronous narration and online video applications, which are among the teaching methods suitable for distance education. Research shows that when students learn the material in an active learning environment, they understand the material at a deeper level and thus retain it for a longer period of time. In order to facilitate the active learning component of the course, question-answer and discussion-based learning activities will be included. These activities aim to answer discussion questions, support in-class exercises and group work.</Data></Cell>
<Cell ss:StyleID="Text"><Data ss:Type="String">https://obs.acibadem.edu.tr/oibs/bologna/progCourseDetails.aspx?curCourse=421790&amp;lang=en</Data></Cell>
<Cell ss:StyleID="Text"><Data ss:Type="String">OK</Data></Cell>
<Cell ss:StyleID="Text"><Data ss:Type="String"></Data></Cell>
</Row>
<Row>
<Cell ss:StyleID="Text"><Data ss:Type="String">Nutrition and Dietetics</Data></Cell>
<Cell ss:StyleID="Text"><Data ss:Type="String">4</Data></Cell>
<Cell ss:StyleID="Text"><Data ss:Type="String">BES 130</Data></Cell>
<Cell ss:StyleID="Text"><Data ss:Type="String">Sociology</Data></Cell>
<Cell ss:StyleID="Text"><Data ss:Type="String">2</Data></Cell>
<Cell ss:StyleID="Text"><Data ss:Type="String">2+0+0</Data></Cell>
<Cell ss:StyleID="Text"><Data ss:Type="String">2</Data></Cell>
<Cell ss:StyleID="Text"><Data ss:Type="String">3</Data></Cell>
<Cell ss:StyleID="Text"><Data ss:Type="String">19.08.2025</Data></Cell>
<Cell ss:StyleID="Text"><Data ss:Type="String">This course includes the following topics: Definition of Sociology, Subject, Purpose, Limits, Birth and History of Sociology in the World and in Türkiye, Relationship with Other Sciences, Basic Approaches in Sociology, Basic Concepts of Sociology, Society, Individual and Society, Society and Culture, Socialization, Behavioral Patterns, Social Control Mechanisms, Social Change, Globalization and Social Effects, Modernism, Development, Underdevelopment, Social Stratification, Social Mobility, Settlement Pattern, Population.</Data></Cell>
<Cell ss:StyleID="Text"><Data ss:Type="String">https://obs.acibadem.edu.tr/oibs/bologna/progCourseDetails.aspx?curCourse=421963&amp;lang=en</Data></Cell>
<Cell ss:StyleID="Text"><Data ss:Type="String">OK</Data></Cell>
<Cell ss:StyleID="Text"><Data ss:Type="String"></Data></Cell>
</Row>
<Row>
<Cell ss:StyleID="Text"><Data ss:Type="String">Nutrition and Dietetics</Data></Cell>
<Cell ss:StyleID="Text"><Data ss:Type="String">4</Data></Cell>
<Cell ss:StyleID="Text"><Data ss:Type="String">BES 225</Data></Cell>
<Cell ss:StyleID="Text"><Data ss:Type="String">Food Chemistry and Application I</Data></Cell>
<Cell ss:StyleID="Text"><Data ss:Type="String">3</Data></Cell>
<Cell ss:StyleID="Text"><Data ss:Type="String">2+2+0</Data></Cell>
<Cell ss:StyleID="Text"><Data ss:Type="String">3</Data></Cell>
<Cell ss:StyleID="Text"><Data ss:Type="String">5</Data></Cell>
<Cell ss:StyleID="Text"><Data ss:Type="String">19.08.2025</Data></Cell>
<Cell ss:StyleID="Text"><Data ss:Type="String">The scope of the course is to use the physical, chemical and functional properties of macronutrients such as water, carbohydrate, protein and fat, enzyme, pigment, taste and odor components of foods and basic qualitative and quantitative methods used in nutrient analysis. It supports the foundation of vocational courses in the second and third grades. The course makes a significant contribution to the acquisition of the knowledge, skills and competencies required for graduation.</Data></Cell>
<Cell ss:StyleID="Text"><Data ss:Type="String">https://obs.acibadem.edu.tr/oibs/bologna/progCourseDetails.aspx?curCourse=421888&amp;lang=en</Data></Cell>
<Cell ss:StyleID="Text"><Data ss:Type="String">OK</Data></Cell>
<Cell ss:StyleID="Text"><Data ss:Type="String"></Data></Cell>
</Row>
<Row>
<Cell ss:StyleID="Text"><Data ss:Type="String">Nutrition and Dietetics</Data></Cell>
<Cell ss:StyleID="Text"><Data ss:Type="String">4</Data></Cell>
<Cell ss:StyleID="Text"><Data ss:Type="String">BES 227</Data></Cell>
<Cell ss:StyleID="Text"><Data ss:Type="String">Principles of Nutrition I</Data></Cell>
<Cell ss:StyleID="Text"><Data ss:Type="String">3</Data></Cell>
<Cell ss:StyleID="Text"><Data ss:Type="String">3+2+0</Data></Cell>
<Cell ss:StyleID="Text"><Data ss:Type="String">4</Data></Cell>
<Cell ss:StyleID="Text"><Data ss:Type="String">4</Data></Cell>
<Cell ss:StyleID="Text"><Data ss:Type="String">02.10.2025</Data></Cell>
<Cell ss:StyleID="Text"><Data ss:Type="String">The content of this theoretical course consists of the functions and requirements of macronutrients, diseases/disorders caused by insufficient or excessive intake. The course will be conducted face-to-face and remotely, and online quizzes, which are mobile learning methods, will be made to facilitate learning.</Data></Cell>
<Cell ss:StyleID="Text"><Data ss:Type="String">https://obs.acibadem.edu.tr/oibs/bologna/progCourseDetails.aspx?curCourse=421772&amp;lang=en</Data></Cell>
<Cell ss:StyleID="Text"><Data ss:Type="String">OK</Data></Cell>
<Cell ss:StyleID="Text"><Data ss:Type="String"></Data></Cell>
</Row>
<Row>
<Cell ss:StyleID="Text"><Data ss:Type="String">Nutrition and Dietetics</Data></Cell>
<Cell ss:StyleID="Text"><Data ss:Type="String">4</Data></Cell>
<Cell ss:StyleID="Text"><Data ss:Type="String">BES 229</Data></Cell>
<Cell ss:StyleID="Text"><Data ss:Type="String">General Microbiology</Data></Cell>
<Cell ss:StyleID="Text"><Data ss:Type="String">3</Data></Cell>
<Cell ss:StyleID="Text"><Data ss:Type="String">2+2+0</Data></Cell>
<Cell ss:StyleID="Text"><Data ss:Type="String">3</Data></Cell>
<Cell ss:StyleID="Text"><Data ss:Type="String">3</Data></Cell>
<Cell ss:StyleID="Text"><Data ss:Type="String">02.10.2025</Data></Cell>
<Cell ss:StyleID="Text"><Data ss:Type="String">The content of the course includes the definition of the structure, metabolism and genetic characteristics of bacteria; It covers the identification of host-parasite relationships. In addition, sterilization in the course content. Defining disinfection methods is also included. Sharing information about antibiotic action and resistance mechanisms, antigen, antibody structure, definition of immune response mechanisms and important concepts of viruses, fungi and parasites in microbiology are given. At the end of this course, it is aimed that students will have general knowledge about general microbiology. The course will be taught face-to-face.</Data></Cell>
<Cell ss:StyleID="Text"><Data ss:Type="String">https://obs.acibadem.edu.tr/oibs/bologna/progCourseDetails.aspx?curCourse=421908&amp;lang=en</Data></Cell>
<Cell ss:StyleID="Text"><Data ss:Type="String">OK</Data></Cell>
<Cell ss:StyleID="Text"><Data ss:Type="String"></Data></Cell>
</Row>
<Row>
<Cell ss:StyleID="Text"><Data ss:Type="String">Nutrition and Dietetics</Data></Cell>
<Cell ss:StyleID="Text"><Data ss:Type="String">4</Data></Cell>
<Cell ss:StyleID="Text"><Data ss:Type="String">BES 251</Data></Cell>
<Cell ss:StyleID="Text"><Data ss:Type="String">Nutritional Biochemistry I</Data></Cell>
<Cell ss:StyleID="Text"><Data ss:Type="String">3</Data></Cell>
<Cell ss:StyleID="Text"><Data ss:Type="String">3+0+0</Data></Cell>
<Cell ss:StyleID="Text"><Data ss:Type="String">3</Data></Cell>
<Cell ss:StyleID="Text"><Data ss:Type="String">5</Data></Cell>
<Cell ss:StyleID="Text"><Data ss:Type="String">02.10.2025</Data></Cell>
<Cell ss:StyleID="Text"><Data ss:Type="String">The theoretical scope of the course forms the basis of third and fourth year vocational courses and professional practices. The course makes a significant contribution to the acquisition of knowledge, skills and competencies required for graduation.
The course will be conducted with online education method, therefore it will be carried out with teaching methods suitable for online education.
During the course, the metabolism of macronutrients in the body, their advanced functions and their vital importance will be explained in weeks.
Research shows that when students learn the material in an active learning environment, they understand the material at a deeper level and thus retain it for a longer period of time.
In order to facilitate the active learning component of the course, there will be questions that help to think and integrate the learned information and to draw a conceptual map in the brain.
With this method, it will strengthen the learning skills of the students and the permanence of the knowledge in learning the basis of the metabolism of macro and micro nutrients inside and outside the classroom.</Data></Cell>
<Cell ss:StyleID="Text"><Data ss:Type="String">https://obs.acibadem.edu.tr/oibs/bologna/progCourseDetails.aspx?curCourse=421887&amp;lang=en</Data></Cell>
<Cell ss:StyleID="Text"><Data ss:Type="String">OK</Data></Cell>
<Cell ss:StyleID="Text"><Data ss:Type="String"></Data></Cell>
</Row>
<Row>
<Cell ss:StyleID="Text"><Data ss:Type="String">Nutrition and Dietetics</Data></Cell>
<Cell ss:StyleID="Text"><Data ss:Type="String">4</Data></Cell>
<Cell ss:StyleID="Text"><Data ss:Type="String">BES 253</Data></Cell>
<Cell ss:StyleID="Text"><Data ss:Type="String">Principles of Food, Preparation and Cooking Practices I</Data></Cell>
<Cell ss:StyleID="Text"><Data ss:Type="String">3</Data></Cell>
<Cell ss:StyleID="Text"><Data ss:Type="String">2+2+0</Data></Cell>
<Cell ss:StyleID="Text"><Data ss:Type="String">3</Data></Cell>
<Cell ss:StyleID="Text"><Data ss:Type="String">4</Data></Cell>
<Cell ss:StyleID="Text"><Data ss:Type="String">19.08.2025</Data></Cell>
<Cell ss:StyleID="Text"><Data ss:Type="String">TThe theoretical and practical scope of the course consists of foods, food groups, food preparation and cooking methods. The course makes a significant contribution to the acquisition of knowledge, skills and competencies required for graduation.</Data></Cell>
<Cell ss:StyleID="Text"><Data ss:Type="String">https://obs.acibadem.edu.tr/oibs/bologna/progCourseDetails.aspx?curCourse=421782&amp;lang=en</Data></Cell>
<Cell ss:StyleID="Text"><Data ss:Type="String">OK</Data></Cell>
<Cell ss:StyleID="Text"><Data ss:Type="String"></Data></Cell>
</Row>
<Row>
<Cell ss:StyleID="Text"><Data ss:Type="String">Nutrition and Dietetics</Data></Cell>
<Cell ss:StyleID="Text"><Data ss:Type="String">4</Data></Cell>
<Cell ss:StyleID="Text"><Data ss:Type="String">ING 201</Data></Cell>
<Cell ss:StyleID="Text"><Data ss:Type="String">English III</Data></Cell>
<Cell ss:StyleID="Text"><Data ss:Type="String">3</Data></Cell>
<Cell ss:StyleID="Text"><Data ss:Type="String">1+4+0</Data></Cell>
<Cell ss:StyleID="Text"><Data ss:Type="String">3</Data></Cell>
<Cell ss:StyleID="Text"><Data ss:Type="String">3</Data></Cell>
<Cell ss:StyleID="Text"><Data ss:Type="String">15.10.2025</Data></Cell>
<Cell ss:StyleID="Text"><Data ss:Type="String">Pre-intermediate - A2+/B1</Data></Cell>
<Cell ss:StyleID="Text"><Data ss:Type="String">https://obs.acibadem.edu.tr/oibs/bologna/progCourseDetails.aspx?curCourse=421925&amp;lang=en</Data></Cell>
<Cell ss:StyleID="Text"><Data ss:Type="String">OK</Data></Cell>
<Cell ss:StyleID="Text"><Data ss:Type="String"></Data></Cell>
</Row>
<Row>
<Cell ss:StyleID="Text"><Data ss:Type="String">Nutrition and Dietetics</Data></Cell>
<Cell ss:StyleID="Text"><Data ss:Type="String">4</Data></Cell>
<Cell ss:StyleID="Text"><Data ss:Type="String">BES 231</Data></Cell>
<Cell ss:StyleID="Text"><Data ss:Type="String">Accessing Evidence-Based Information and Academic Writing Skills</Data></Cell>
<Cell ss:StyleID="Text"><Data ss:Type="String">3</Data></Cell>
<Cell ss:StyleID="Text"><Data ss:Type="String">2+0+0</Data></Cell>
<Cell ss:StyleID="Text"><Data ss:Type="String">2</Data></Cell>
<Cell ss:StyleID="Text"><Data ss:Type="String">3</Data></Cell>
<Cell ss:StyleID="Text"><Data ss:Type="String">25.09.2025</Data></Cell>
<Cell ss:StyleID="Text"><Data ss:Type="String">The theoretical scope of the course is the basis of vocational courses, professional practices and branches of science supporting this field in the field of nutrition and dietetics in the 3rd and 4th grades. The course contributes to the integration of field and non-field theoretical and applied knowledge, the correct use of scientific literature, access to evidence-based information and the development of academic writing skills. It contributes to the acquisition of necessary knowledge, skills and competencies for the planning of the nutritional care process and its implementation within the framework of ethical principles. The course will be conducted face to face. In this course, in which student-centered education is used intensively, question-answer, practice and discussion-based learning activities and discussion of the feedback of the given assignments will be included in order to facilitate the active learning component of the course.</Data></Cell>
<Cell ss:StyleID="Text"><Data ss:Type="String">https://obs.acibadem.edu.tr/oibs/bologna/progCourseDetails.aspx?curCourse=421770&amp;lang=en</Data></Cell>
<Cell ss:StyleID="Text"><Data ss:Type="String">OK</Data></Cell>
<Cell ss:StyleID="Text"><Data ss:Type="String"></Data></Cell>
</Row>
<Row>
<Cell ss:StyleID="Text"><Data ss:Type="String">Nutrition and Dietetics</Data></Cell>
<Cell ss:StyleID="Text"><Data ss:Type="String">4</Data></Cell>
<Cell ss:StyleID="Text"><Data ss:Type="String">BES 228</Data></Cell>
<Cell ss:StyleID="Text"><Data ss:Type="String">Principles of Nutrition II</Data></Cell>
<Cell ss:StyleID="Text"><Data ss:Type="String">4</Data></Cell>
<Cell ss:StyleID="Text"><Data ss:Type="String">3+2+0</Data></Cell>
<Cell ss:StyleID="Text"><Data ss:Type="String">4</Data></Cell>
<Cell ss:StyleID="Text"><Data ss:Type="String">4</Data></Cell>
<Cell ss:StyleID="Text"><Data ss:Type="String">19.08.2025</Data></Cell>
<Cell ss:StyleID="Text"><Data ss:Type="String">The content of this theoretical course consists of the functions and requirements of micronutrients, diseases/disorders caused by insufficient or excessive intake, and water and electrolytes. The course will be conducted face-to-face and remotely, and online quizzes, which are mobile learning methods, will be made to facilitate learning.</Data></Cell>
<Cell ss:StyleID="Text"><Data ss:Type="String">https://obs.acibadem.edu.tr/oibs/bologna/progCourseDetails.aspx?curCourse=421812&amp;lang=en</Data></Cell>
<Cell ss:StyleID="Text"><Data ss:Type="String">OK</Data></Cell>
<Cell ss:StyleID="Text"><Data ss:Type="String"></Data></Cell>
</Row>
<Row>
<Cell ss:StyleID="Text"><Data ss:Type="String">Nutrition and Dietetics</Data></Cell>
<Cell ss:StyleID="Text"><Data ss:Type="String">4</Data></Cell>
<Cell ss:StyleID="Text"><Data ss:Type="String">BES 230</Data></Cell>
<Cell ss:StyleID="Text"><Data ss:Type="String">Food Chemistry and Practices II</Data></Cell>
<Cell ss:StyleID="Text"><Data ss:Type="String">4</Data></Cell>
<Cell ss:StyleID="Text"><Data ss:Type="String">2+2+0</Data></Cell>
<Cell ss:StyleID="Text"><Data ss:Type="String">3</Data></Cell>
<Cell ss:StyleID="Text"><Data ss:Type="String">5</Data></Cell>
<Cell ss:StyleID="Text"><Data ss:Type="String">19.08.2025</Data></Cell>
<Cell ss:StyleID="Text"><Data ss:Type="String">The scope of the course is to learn the effects of minerals and vitamins on food chemistry processes, the methods used in the evaluation of food quality, the structural and functional properties of basic food groups (milk, meat, eggs) and the effects of functional foods on health. It supports the foundation of vocational courses in the second and third grades. The course makes a significant contribution to the acquisition of the knowledge, skills and competencies required for graduation.</Data></Cell>
<Cell ss:StyleID="Text"><Data ss:Type="String">https://obs.acibadem.edu.tr/oibs/bologna/progCourseDetails.aspx?curCourse=421816&amp;lang=en</Data></Cell>
<Cell ss:StyleID="Text"><Data ss:Type="String">OK</Data></Cell>
<Cell ss:StyleID="Text"><Data ss:Type="String"></Data></Cell>
</Row>
<Row>
<Cell ss:StyleID="Text"><Data ss:Type="String">Nutrition and Dietetics</Data></Cell>
<Cell ss:StyleID="Text"><Data ss:Type="String">4</Data></Cell>
<Cell ss:StyleID="Text"><Data ss:Type="String">BES 250</Data></Cell>
<Cell ss:StyleID="Text"><Data ss:Type="String">Demographical Structure and Health</Data></Cell>
<Cell ss:StyleID="Text"><Data ss:Type="String">4</Data></Cell>
<Cell ss:StyleID="Text"><Data ss:Type="String">2+0+0</Data></Cell>
<Cell ss:StyleID="Text"><Data ss:Type="String">2</Data></Cell>
<Cell ss:StyleID="Text"><Data ss:Type="String">3</Data></Cell>
<Cell ss:StyleID="Text"><Data ss:Type="String">19.08.2025</Data></Cell>
<Cell ss:StyleID="Text"><Data ss:Type="String">The theoretical scope of the course forms the basis of social communication after graduation.
The course makes a significant contribution to the acquisition of knowledge, skills and competencies required for graduation. The course content has been prepared with the aim of protecting, improving and developing public health.
In addition, it is aimed to gain the ability to critically examine the criteria that determine the level of public health. The course will be conducted in an online education environment, therefore it will be carried out with teaching methods suitable for distance education.
Research shows that when students learn the material in an active learning environment, they understand the material at a deeper level and thus retain it for a longer period of time.
In order to facilitate the active learning component of the course, question-answer learning technique will be included. This technique strengthens critical answering of discussion questions, in-class exercises and group work.</Data></Cell>
<Cell ss:StyleID="Text"><Data ss:Type="String">https://obs.acibadem.edu.tr/oibs/bologna/progCourseDetails.aspx?curCourse=421817&amp;lang=en</Data></Cell>
<Cell ss:StyleID="Text"><Data ss:Type="String">OK</Data></Cell>
<Cell ss:StyleID="Text"><Data ss:Type="String"></Data></Cell>
</Row>
<Row>
<Cell ss:StyleID="Text"><Data ss:Type="String">Nutrition and Dietetics</Data></Cell>
<Cell ss:StyleID="Text"><Data ss:Type="String">4</Data></Cell>
<Cell ss:StyleID="Text"><Data ss:Type="String">BES 252</Data></Cell>
<Cell ss:StyleID="Text"><Data ss:Type="String">Nutritional Biochemistry II</Data></Cell>
<Cell ss:StyleID="Text"><Data ss:Type="String">4</Data></Cell>
<Cell ss:StyleID="Text"><Data ss:Type="String">3+0+0</Data></Cell>
<Cell ss:StyleID="Text"><Data ss:Type="String">3</Data></Cell>
<Cell ss:StyleID="Text"><Data ss:Type="String">5</Data></Cell>
<Cell ss:StyleID="Text"><Data ss:Type="String">19.08.2025</Data></Cell>
<Cell ss:StyleID="Text"><Data ss:Type="String">The theoretical scope of the course forms the basis of third and fourth year vocational courses and professional practices. The course makes a significant contribution to the acquisition of knowledge, skills and competencies required for graduation.
The course will be conducted with hybrid education method, therefore it will be carried out with teaching methods suitable for online and face-to-face education. During the course, the metabolism of micronutrients in the body, their advanced functions and their relations with macronutrients will be explained in weeks.
Research shows that when students learn the material in an active learning environment, they understand the material at a deeper level and thus retain it for a longer period of time.
In order to facilitate the active learning component of the course, there will be questions that help to think and integrate the learned information and to draw a conceptual map in the brain.
With this method, it will strengthen the learning skills of the students and the permanence of the knowledge in learning the basis of the metabolism of macro and micro nutrients inside and outside the classroom.</Data></Cell>
<Cell ss:StyleID="Text"><Data ss:Type="String">https://obs.acibadem.edu.tr/oibs/bologna/progCourseDetails.aspx?curCourse=421819&amp;lang=en</Data></Cell>
<Cell ss:StyleID="Text"><Data ss:Type="String">OK</Data></Cell>
<Cell ss:StyleID="Text"><Data ss:Type="String"></Data></Cell>
</Row>
<Row>
<Cell ss:StyleID="Text"><Data ss:Type="String">Nutrition and Dietetics</Data></Cell>
<Cell ss:StyleID="Text"><Data ss:Type="String">4</Data></Cell>
<Cell ss:StyleID="Text"><Data ss:Type="String">BES 254</Data></Cell>
<Cell ss:StyleID="Text"><Data ss:Type="String">Principles of Food, Preparation and Cooking Practices II</Data></Cell>
<Cell ss:StyleID="Text"><Data ss:Type="String">4</Data></Cell>
<Cell ss:StyleID="Text"><Data ss:Type="String">2+2+0</Data></Cell>
<Cell ss:StyleID="Text"><Data ss:Type="String">3</Data></Cell>
<Cell ss:StyleID="Text"><Data ss:Type="String">4</Data></Cell>
<Cell ss:StyleID="Text"><Data ss:Type="String">19.08.2025</Data></Cell>
<Cell ss:StyleID="Text"><Data ss:Type="String">The theoretical and practical scope of the course consists of foods, food groups, food preparation and cooking methods. The course makes a significant contribution to the acquisition of knowledge, skills and competencies required for graduation.</Data></Cell>
<Cell ss:StyleID="Text"><Data ss:Type="String">https://obs.acibadem.edu.tr/oibs/bologna/progCourseDetails.aspx?curCourse=421815&amp;lang=en</Data></Cell>
<Cell ss:StyleID="Text"><Data ss:Type="String">OK</Data></Cell>
<Cell ss:StyleID="Text"><Data ss:Type="String"></Data></Cell>
</Row>
<Row>
<Cell ss:StyleID="Text"><Data ss:Type="String">Nutrition and Dietetics</Data></Cell>
<Cell ss:StyleID="Text"><Data ss:Type="String">4</Data></Cell>
<Cell ss:StyleID="Text"><Data ss:Type="String">BES 258</Data></Cell>
<Cell ss:StyleID="Text"><Data ss:Type="String">Food Microbiology</Data></Cell>
<Cell ss:StyleID="Text"><Data ss:Type="String">4</Data></Cell>
<Cell ss:StyleID="Text"><Data ss:Type="String">2+0+0</Data></Cell>
<Cell ss:StyleID="Text"><Data ss:Type="String">2</Data></Cell>
<Cell ss:StyleID="Text"><Data ss:Type="String">3</Data></Cell>
<Cell ss:StyleID="Text"><Data ss:Type="String">19.08.2025</Data></Cell>
<Cell ss:StyleID="Text"><Data ss:Type="String">The content of the course consists of examining the relationship between microorganisms and nutrients, determining potential risks, and determining hygiene and sanitation conditions. At the end of this course, it is aimed that students will have general information about determining general risks, preventing poisoning in individual/collective food services, and providing the necessary hygiene conditions. The course will be taught face-to-face.</Data></Cell>
<Cell ss:StyleID="Text"><Data ss:Type="String">https://obs.acibadem.edu.tr/oibs/bologna/progCourseDetails.aspx?curCourse=421862&amp;lang=en</Data></Cell>
<Cell ss:StyleID="Text"><Data ss:Type="String">OK</Data></Cell>
<Cell ss:StyleID="Text"><Data ss:Type="String"></Data></Cell>
</Row>
<Row>
<Cell ss:StyleID="Text"><Data ss:Type="String">Nutrition and Dietetics</Data></Cell>
<Cell ss:StyleID="Text"><Data ss:Type="String">4</Data></Cell>
<Cell ss:StyleID="Text"><Data ss:Type="String">ING 202</Data></Cell>
<Cell ss:StyleID="Text"><Data ss:Type="String">English IV</Data></Cell>
<Cell ss:StyleID="Text"><Data ss:Type="String">4</Data></Cell>
<Cell ss:StyleID="Text"><Data ss:Type="String">1+4+0</Data></Cell>
<Cell ss:StyleID="Text"><Data ss:Type="String">3</Data></Cell>
<Cell ss:StyleID="Text"><Data ss:Type="String">3</Data></Cell>
<Cell ss:StyleID="Text"><Data ss:Type="String">20.02.2026</Data></Cell>
<Cell ss:StyleID="Text"><Data ss:Type="String">The theoretical and practical scope of the course contributes to the foundation of professional English knowledge. The course makes a significant contribution to the acquisition of the knowledge, skills and competencies required for graduation. The course will be conducted in a distance education environment, therefore it will be carried out with teaching methods suitable for online education. In order to facilitate the active learning component of the course, synchronous lecture, homework, question-answer, discussion-based learning activities will be included.</Data></Cell>
<Cell ss:StyleID="Text"><Data ss:Type="String">https://obs.acibadem.edu.tr/oibs/bologna/progCourseDetails.aspx?curCourse=421926&amp;lang=en</Data></Cell>
<Cell ss:StyleID="Text"><Data ss:Type="String">OK</Data></Cell>
<Cell ss:StyleID="Text"><Data ss:Type="String"></Data></Cell>
</Row>
<Row>
<Cell ss:StyleID="Text"><Data ss:Type="String">Nutrition and Dietetics</Data></Cell>
<Cell ss:StyleID="Text"><Data ss:Type="String">4</Data></Cell>
<Cell ss:StyleID="Text"><Data ss:Type="String">BES 317</Data></Cell>
<Cell ss:StyleID="Text"><Data ss:Type="String">Nutritional Assesment of Community</Data></Cell>
<Cell ss:StyleID="Text"><Data ss:Type="String">5</Data></Cell>
<Cell ss:StyleID="Text"><Data ss:Type="String">3+0+0</Data></Cell>
<Cell ss:StyleID="Text"><Data ss:Type="String">3</Data></Cell>
<Cell ss:StyleID="Text"><Data ss:Type="String">2</Data></Cell>
<Cell ss:StyleID="Text"><Data ss:Type="String">13.11.2025</Data></Cell>
<Cell ss:StyleID="Text"><Data ss:Type="String">The theoretical scope of the course forms the basis for professional courses, professional practices, and supporting scientific disciplines in the field of Nutrition and Dietetics in the third and fourth years. It includes methods for assessing nutritional status, anthropometric measurements, biochemical findings, biophysical methods, determining body composition, nutritional screening tests, food consumption research methods, and sample anthropometric laboratory applications. To facilitate the active learning component of the course, question-and-answer and discussion-based learning activities will be included. These activities aim to support answering discussion questions, in-class exercises, and group work.</Data></Cell>
<Cell ss:StyleID="Text"><Data ss:Type="String">https://obs.acibadem.edu.tr/oibs/bologna/progCourseDetails.aspx?curCourse=421846&amp;lang=en</Data></Cell>
<Cell ss:StyleID="Text"><Data ss:Type="String">OK</Data></Cell>
<Cell ss:StyleID="Text"><Data ss:Type="String"></Data></Cell>
</Row>
<Row>
<Cell ss:StyleID="Text"><Data ss:Type="String">Nutrition and Dietetics</Data></Cell>
<Cell ss:StyleID="Text"><Data ss:Type="String">4</Data></Cell>
<Cell ss:StyleID="Text"><Data ss:Type="String">BES 319</Data></Cell>
<Cell ss:StyleID="Text"><Data ss:Type="String">Mother and Child Nutrition</Data></Cell>
<Cell ss:StyleID="Text"><Data ss:Type="String">5</Data></Cell>
<Cell ss:StyleID="Text"><Data ss:Type="String">2+2+0</Data></Cell>
<Cell ss:StyleID="Text"><Data ss:Type="String">3</Data></Cell>
<Cell ss:StyleID="Text"><Data ss:Type="String">2</Data></Cell>
<Cell ss:StyleID="Text"><Data ss:Type="String">04.12.2025</Data></Cell>
<Cell ss:StyleID="Text"><Data ss:Type="String">The theoretical and practical scope of the course forms the basis of the fourth year applied vocational courses and professional practices. The importance of child nutrition in the world and in Turkey, physiological and metabolic changes during pregnancy and lactation, nutrition-related problems, energy and nutrient requirements, breastfeeding success, infant and young child nutrition, complementary feeding practices, preschool period, school age and It is aimed to gain knowledge and skills about adolescent nutrition and problems encountered in these periods, energy and nutrient requirements and principles of healthy eating, evaluation of growth, obesity and malnutrition. In this context, the course will be carried out interactively with in-class activities, course materials and application activities will be shared through LMS. In order to increase learning effectiveness, learning based on case solving, demonstration, question-answer lecture techniques will be used in the course through an active learning environment.</Data></Cell>
<Cell ss:StyleID="Text"><Data ss:Type="String">https://obs.acibadem.edu.tr/oibs/bologna/progCourseDetails.aspx?curCourse=421896&amp;lang=en</Data></Cell>
<Cell ss:StyleID="Text"><Data ss:Type="String">OK</Data></Cell>
<Cell ss:StyleID="Text"><Data ss:Type="String"></Data></Cell>
</Row>
<Row>
<Cell ss:StyleID="Text"><Data ss:Type="String">Nutrition and Dietetics</Data></Cell>
<Cell ss:StyleID="Text"><Data ss:Type="String">4</Data></Cell>
<Cell ss:StyleID="Text"><Data ss:Type="String">BES 343</Data></Cell>
<Cell ss:StyleID="Text"><Data ss:Type="String">Nutritional and Dietetic Practice in Pediatric Diseases I</Data></Cell>
<Cell ss:StyleID="Text"><Data ss:Type="String">5</Data></Cell>
<Cell ss:StyleID="Text"><Data ss:Type="String">2+2+0</Data></Cell>
<Cell ss:StyleID="Text"><Data ss:Type="String">3</Data></Cell>
<Cell ss:StyleID="Text"><Data ss:Type="String">4</Data></Cell>
<Cell ss:StyleID="Text"><Data ss:Type="String">04.12.2025</Data></Cell>
<Cell ss:StyleID="Text"><Data ss:Type="String">The theoretical scope of the course is the basis of the fourth year applied vocational courses and professional practices. Enteral parenteral nutrition in prematurity, infancy and childhood, acute gastroenteritis, malnutrition, malabsorptions, infectious diseases, childhood obesity, metabolic syndrome, eating behavior disorders and medical nutrition therapies. aimed at gaining knowledge and skills. In this context, the course will be conducted interactively with in-class activities, and course materials and application activities will be shared through LMS. In order to increase learning efficiency, learning based on case solving, demonstration, question-answer lecture techniques will be used in the course through an active learning environment.</Data></Cell>
<Cell ss:StyleID="Text"><Data ss:Type="String">https://obs.acibadem.edu.tr/oibs/bologna/progCourseDetails.aspx?curCourse=421894&amp;lang=en</Data></Cell>
<Cell ss:StyleID="Text"><Data ss:Type="String">OK</Data></Cell>
<Cell ss:StyleID="Text"><Data ss:Type="String"></Data></Cell>
</Row>
<Row>
<Cell ss:StyleID="Text"><Data ss:Type="String">Nutrition and Dietetics</Data></Cell>
<Cell ss:StyleID="Text"><Data ss:Type="String">4</Data></Cell>
<Cell ss:StyleID="Text"><Data ss:Type="String">BES 345</Data></Cell>
<Cell ss:StyleID="Text"><Data ss:Type="String">Food Control and Legislation</Data></Cell>
<Cell ss:StyleID="Text"><Data ss:Type="String">5</Data></Cell>
<Cell ss:StyleID="Text"><Data ss:Type="String">2+0+0</Data></Cell>
<Cell ss:StyleID="Text"><Data ss:Type="String">2</Data></Cell>
<Cell ss:StyleID="Text"><Data ss:Type="String">1</Data></Cell>
<Cell ss:StyleID="Text"><Data ss:Type="String">05.12.2025</Data></Cell>
<Cell ss:StyleID="Text"><Data ss:Type="String">The theoretical scope of the course forms the basis of the fourth year applied vocational courses and professional practices. The course makes a significant contribution to the acquisition of the necessary knowledge, skills and competencies in food control, food quality, Turkish food codex, food additives, drug residues, pesticide residues for graduation. The course will be conducted in a distance education environment, so it will be carried out with teaching methods suitable for online education, and online video/exam applications. Research shows that when students learn material in an active learning environment, they understand the material at a deeper level and thus retain it longer. To facilitate the active learning component of the course, lecture, synchronous, presentation/demonstration, discussion-based learning, homework, question/answer learning techniques will be used.</Data></Cell>
<Cell ss:StyleID="Text"><Data ss:Type="String">https://obs.acibadem.edu.tr/oibs/bologna/progCourseDetails.aspx?curCourse=421895&amp;lang=en</Data></Cell>
<Cell ss:StyleID="Text"><Data ss:Type="String">OK</Data></Cell>
<Cell ss:StyleID="Text"><Data ss:Type="String"></Data></Cell>
</Row>
<Row>
<Cell ss:StyleID="Text"><Data ss:Type="String">Nutrition and Dietetics</Data></Cell>
<Cell ss:StyleID="Text"><Data ss:Type="String">4</Data></Cell>
<Cell ss:StyleID="Text"><Data ss:Type="String">BES 349</Data></Cell>
<Cell ss:StyleID="Text"><Data ss:Type="String">Institutional Food Services I</Data></Cell>
<Cell ss:StyleID="Text"><Data ss:Type="String">5</Data></Cell>
<Cell ss:StyleID="Text"><Data ss:Type="String">3+0+0</Data></Cell>
<Cell ss:StyleID="Text"><Data ss:Type="String">3</Data></Cell>
<Cell ss:StyleID="Text"><Data ss:Type="String">3</Data></Cell>
<Cell ss:StyleID="Text"><Data ss:Type="String">05.12.2025</Data></Cell>
<Cell ss:StyleID="Text"><Data ss:Type="String">The theoretical and practical scope of the course forms the basis of the fourth year applied vocational courses and professional practices. The course contributes significantly to the acquisition of the knowledge, skills and competencies required for graduation in the subjects of food purchasing, storage, management and organization and menu planning principles in public nutrition systems. Research shows that when students learn material in an active learning environment, they understand the material at a deeper level and thus retain it longer. To facilitate the active learning component of the course, lecture, synchronous, presentation/demonstration, discussion-based learning, homework, question/answer learning techniques will be used.</Data></Cell>
<Cell ss:StyleID="Text"><Data ss:Type="String">https://obs.acibadem.edu.tr/oibs/bologna/progCourseDetails.aspx?curCourse=421845&amp;lang=en</Data></Cell>
<Cell ss:StyleID="Text"><Data ss:Type="String">OK</Data></Cell>
<Cell ss:StyleID="Text"><Data ss:Type="String"></Data></Cell>
</Row>
<Row>
<Cell ss:StyleID="Text"><Data ss:Type="String">Nutrition and Dietetics</Data></Cell>
<Cell ss:StyleID="Text"><Data ss:Type="String">4</Data></Cell>
<Cell ss:StyleID="Text"><Data ss:Type="String">BES 367</Data></Cell>
<Cell ss:StyleID="Text"><Data ss:Type="String">Nutritional and Dietetic Practice in Adult Diseases I</Data></Cell>
<Cell ss:StyleID="Text"><Data ss:Type="String">5</Data></Cell>
<Cell ss:StyleID="Text"><Data ss:Type="String">4+2+0</Data></Cell>
<Cell ss:StyleID="Text"><Data ss:Type="String">5</Data></Cell>
<Cell ss:StyleID="Text"><Data ss:Type="String">5</Data></Cell>
<Cell ss:StyleID="Text"><Data ss:Type="String">01.12.2025</Data></Cell>
<Cell ss:StyleID="Text"><Data ss:Type="String">The theoretical and practical scope of the course forms the basis of professional courses, professional practices and disciplines in the field of Nutrition and Dietetics. The course contributes to the integration of theoretical and practical knowledge from the field and outside the field, to the planning of scientific research with the use of evidence-based information, to the use of research skills. It contributes to the acquisition of the knowledge, skills and competencies required for the planning of the nutrition care process, autonomous/teamwork, professional advocacy and guidance to colleagues, and the implementation of nutrition education and counseling within the framework of ethical principles. The course will be conducted according to the face-to-face education method. Research shows that when students learn material in an active learning environment, they understand the material at a deeper level and thus retain it for a longer period of time. In order to facilitate the active learning component of the course, case solution-based learning, problem-based learning, discussion-based learning, personal/independent learning, homework, question-answer, brainstorming and observation learning activities will be included. These activities aim to answer discussion questions, support classroom exercises and group work.</Data></Cell>
<Cell ss:StyleID="Text"><Data ss:Type="String">https://obs.acibadem.edu.tr/oibs/bologna/progCourseDetails.aspx?curCourse=421889&amp;lang=en</Data></Cell>
<Cell ss:StyleID="Text"><Data ss:Type="String">OK</Data></Cell>
<Cell ss:StyleID="Text"><Data ss:Type="String"></Data></Cell>
</Row>
<Row>
<Cell ss:StyleID="Text"><Data ss:Type="String">Nutrition and Dietetics</Data></Cell>
<Cell ss:StyleID="Text"><Data ss:Type="String">4</Data></Cell>
<Cell ss:StyleID="Text"><Data ss:Type="String">ING 301</Data></Cell>
<Cell ss:StyleID="Text"><Data ss:Type="String">English V</Data></Cell>
<Cell ss:StyleID="Text"><Data ss:Type="String">5</Data></Cell>
<Cell ss:StyleID="Text"><Data ss:Type="String">2+3+0</Data></Cell>
<Cell ss:StyleID="Text"><Data ss:Type="String">3,5</Data></Cell>
<Cell ss:StyleID="Text"><Data ss:Type="String">4</Data></Cell>
<Cell ss:StyleID="Text"><Data ss:Type="String">20.10.2025</Data></Cell>
<Cell ss:StyleID="Text"><Data ss:Type="String">Intermediate-A2+/B1</Data></Cell>
<Cell ss:StyleID="Text"><Data ss:Type="String">https://obs.acibadem.edu.tr/oibs/bologna/progCourseDetails.aspx?curCourse=421927&amp;lang=en</Data></Cell>
<Cell ss:StyleID="Text"><Data ss:Type="String">OK</Data></Cell>
<Cell ss:StyleID="Text"><Data ss:Type="String"></Data></Cell>
</Row>
<Row>
<Cell ss:StyleID="Text"><Data ss:Type="String">Nutrition and Dietetics</Data></Cell>
<Cell ss:StyleID="Text"><Data ss:Type="String">4</Data></Cell>
<Cell ss:StyleID="Text"><Data ss:Type="String">BES 303</Data></Cell>
<Cell ss:StyleID="Text"><Data ss:Type="String">Management of Children, Adolescent and Adult Obesity</Data></Cell>
<Cell ss:StyleID="Text"><Data ss:Type="String">5</Data></Cell>
<Cell ss:StyleID="Text"><Data ss:Type="String">2+0+0</Data></Cell>
<Cell ss:StyleID="Text"><Data ss:Type="String">2</Data></Cell>
<Cell ss:StyleID="Text"><Data ss:Type="String">3</Data></Cell>
<Cell ss:StyleID="Text"><Data ss:Type="String">19.08.2025</Data></Cell>
<Cell ss:StyleID="Text"><Data ss:Type="String">Obesity ethiology, pathophysiology, medical nutrition therapy</Data></Cell>
