<Row>
<Cell ss:StyleID="Text"><Data ss:Type="String">Nutrition and Dietetics</Data></Cell>
<Cell ss:StyleID="Text"><Data ss:Type="String">4</Data></Cell>
<Cell ss:StyleID="Text"><Data ss:Type="String">BES 346</Data></Cell>
<Cell ss:StyleID="Text"><Data ss:Type="String">Community Nutrition and Epidemiology</Data></Cell>
<Cell ss:StyleID="Text"><Data ss:Type="String">6</Data></Cell>
<Cell ss:StyleID="Text"><Data ss:Type="String">3+0+0</Data></Cell>
<Cell ss:StyleID="Text"><Data ss:Type="String">3</Data></Cell>
<Cell ss:StyleID="Text"><Data ss:Type="String">3</Data></Cell>
<Cell ss:StyleID="Text"><Data ss:Type="String">10.02.2026</Data></Cell>
<Cell ss:StyleID="Text"><Data ss:Type="String">The theoretical scope of the course forms the basis for professional courses, professional practices, and supporting scientific disciplines in the field of Nutrition and Dietetics in the third and fourth years. The course contributes to the integration of theoretical and practical knowledge within and beyond the field by enabling access to evidence-based information, the use of research skills, and the planning of scientific research. The course covers nutrition problems and their epidemiology in Turkey and worldwide, nutrition research, food and nutrition policies, protein -energy malnutrition, obesity, iodine deficiency, iron deficiency, folic acid deficiency, zinc deficiency, vitamin D deficiency and its epidemiology, dental health, nutrition in disaster situations, nutrition in old age, and sustainable nutrition. Research shows that when students learn material in an active learning environment, they understand it at a deeper level and thus retain it longer. To facilitate the active learning component of the course, question-and-answer and discussion-based learning activities will be included. These activities aim to support answering discussion questions, in-class exercises, and group work.</Data></Cell>
<Cell ss:StyleID="Text"><Data ss:Type="String">https://obs.acibadem.edu.tr/oibs/bologna/progCourseDetails.aspx?curCourse=421848&amp;lang=en</Data></Cell>
<Cell ss:StyleID="Text"><Data ss:Type="String">OK</Data></Cell>
<Cell ss:StyleID="Text"><Data ss:Type="String"></Data></Cell>
</Row>
<Row>
<Cell ss:StyleID="Text"><Data ss:Type="String">Nutrition and Dietetics</Data></Cell>
<Cell ss:StyleID="Text"><Data ss:Type="String">4</Data></Cell>
<Cell ss:StyleID="Text"><Data ss:Type="String">BES 350</Data></Cell>
<Cell ss:StyleID="Text"><Data ss:Type="String">Institutional Food Services II</Data></Cell>
<Cell ss:StyleID="Text"><Data ss:Type="String">6</Data></Cell>
<Cell ss:StyleID="Text"><Data ss:Type="String">3+0+0</Data></Cell>
<Cell ss:StyleID="Text"><Data ss:Type="String">3</Data></Cell>
<Cell ss:StyleID="Text"><Data ss:Type="String">3</Data></Cell>
<Cell ss:StyleID="Text"><Data ss:Type="String">10.02.2026</Data></Cell>
<Cell ss:StyleID="Text"><Data ss:Type="String">The theoretical and practical scope of the course forms the basis of the fourth year applied vocational courses and professional practices. The course contributes significantly to the acquisition of the knowledge, skills and competencies required for graduation in kitchen planning, food purchasing, storage, production systems, service methods, cost control, management and organization in mass nutrition systems. Research shows that when students learn material in an active learning environment, they understand the material at a deeper level and thus retain it longer. To facilitate the active learning component of the course, lecture, synchronous, presentation/demonstration, discussion-based learning, homework, question/answer learning techniques will be used.</Data></Cell>
<Cell ss:StyleID="Text"><Data ss:Type="String">https://obs.acibadem.edu.tr/oibs/bologna/progCourseDetails.aspx?curCourse=421863&amp;lang=en</Data></Cell>
<Cell ss:StyleID="Text"><Data ss:Type="String">OK</Data></Cell>
<Cell ss:StyleID="Text"><Data ss:Type="String"></Data></Cell>
</Row>
