<Row>
<Cell ss:StyleID="Text"><Data ss:Type="String">Nutrition and Dietetics</Data></Cell>
<Cell ss:StyleID="Text"><Data ss:Type="String">4</Data></Cell>
<Cell ss:StyleID="Text"><Data ss:Type="String">BES 445</Data></Cell>
<Cell ss:StyleID="Text"><Data ss:Type="String">Vocational Training in Community Nutrition</Data></Cell>
<Cell ss:StyleID="Text"><Data ss:Type="String">7</Data></Cell>
<Cell ss:StyleID="Text"><Data ss:Type="String">0+22+0</Data></Cell>
<Cell ss:StyleID="Text"><Data ss:Type="String">11</Data></Cell>
<Cell ss:StyleID="Text"><Data ss:Type="String">6</Data></Cell>
<Cell ss:StyleID="Text"><Data ss:Type="String">19.08.2025</Data></Cell>
<Cell ss:StyleID="Text"><Data ss:Type="String">The scope of the course includes vocational orientation, assessment of nutritional status in the community and the use of assessment methods.
In line with the target, it is aimed that students will continue their personal development by transferring the theoretical knowledge they have acquired into practice, improve their ability to make the right decision, and gain experience on the job. In line with these objectives, the course is evaluated with oral presentation and research / graduation project methods.
The midterm exam will have a contribution of 40% and the final exam will have a contribution of 60%.
Within the scope of the midterm exam, students develop educational material targeting nutritional problems in the society and present it as a presentation.
For the final evaluation, a research project is expected to be prepared within the scope of this problem.</Data></Cell>
<Cell ss:StyleID="Text"><Data ss:Type="String">https://obs.acibadem.edu.tr/oibs/bologna/progCourseDetails.aspx?curCourse=421917&amp;lang=en</Data></Cell>
<Cell ss:StyleID="Text"><Data ss:Type="String">OK</Data></Cell>
<Cell ss:StyleID="Text"><Data ss:Type="String"></Data></Cell>
</Row>
<Row>
<Cell ss:StyleID="Text"><Data ss:Type="String">Nutrition and Dietetics</Data></Cell>
<Cell ss:StyleID="Text"><Data ss:Type="String">4</Data></Cell>
