<Row>
<Cell ss:StyleID="Text"><Data ss:Type="String">Nutrition and Dietetics</Data></Cell>
<Cell ss:StyleID="Text"><Data ss:Type="String">4</Data></Cell>
<Cell ss:StyleID="Text"><Data ss:Type="String">BES 411</Data></Cell>
<Cell ss:StyleID="Text"><Data ss:Type="String">Bariatric Surgery and Nutritional Therapy</Data></Cell>
<Cell ss:StyleID="Text"><Data ss:Type="String">7</Data></Cell>
<Cell ss:StyleID="Text"><Data ss:Type="String">2+0+0</Data></Cell>
<Cell ss:StyleID="Text"><Data ss:Type="String">2</Data></Cell>
<Cell ss:StyleID="Text"><Data ss:Type="String">3</Data></Cell>
<Cell ss:StyleID="Text"><Data ss:Type="String">02.10.2025</Data></Cell>
<Cell ss:StyleID="Text"><Data ss:Type="String">Topics covered include: definition of obesity, etiology, treatment options; definition of bariatric surgery, indications, contraindications, complications, and the importance of the team; bariatric surgery methods; assessment and monitoring of preoperative and postoperative nutritional status of patients in bariatric surgery; planning of perioperative and postoperative medical nutrition therapy in bariatric surgery; planning of nutritional support programs and supplement use according to bariatric surgery methods; assessment and management of macro/micronutrient deficiencies in bariatric surgery methods; evaluation of metabolic complications in bariatric surgery methods; evaluation of bariatric surgery in metabolic diseases and nutritional interventions to prevent metabolic diseases after bariatric surgery; maintenance and management of weight after bariatric surgery.</Data></Cell>
<Cell ss:StyleID="Text"><Data ss:Type="String">https://obs.acibadem.edu.tr/oibs/bologna/progCourseDetails.aspx?curCourse=421904&amp;lang=en</Data></Cell>
<Cell ss:StyleID="Text"><Data ss:Type="String">OK</Data></Cell>
<Cell ss:StyleID="Text"><Data ss:Type="String"></Data></Cell>
</Row>
