<Row>
<Cell ss:StyleID="Text"><Data ss:Type="String">Nutrition and Dietetics</Data></Cell>
<Cell ss:StyleID="Text"><Data ss:Type="String">4</Data></Cell>
<Cell ss:StyleID="Text"><Data ss:Type="String">BES 470</Data></Cell>
<Cell ss:StyleID="Text"><Data ss:Type="String">Vocational Training in Institutional Food Services</Data></Cell>
<Cell ss:StyleID="Text"><Data ss:Type="String">8</Data></Cell>
<Cell ss:StyleID="Text"><Data ss:Type="String">0+18+0</Data></Cell>
<Cell ss:StyleID="Text"><Data ss:Type="String">9</Data></Cell>
<Cell ss:StyleID="Text"><Data ss:Type="String">7</Data></Cell>
<Cell ss:StyleID="Text"><Data ss:Type="String">03.10.2025</Data></Cell>
<Cell ss:StyleID="Text"><Data ss:Type="String">The student observes the working processes of guide dietitians who work as managers of collective nutrition systems in the institution, adhering to ethical principles and with an understanding of quality, integrates their observations with their theoretical and practical knowledge in the field and out of the field, reports the institutional quality assessment including nutrition systems management practices and shares it in writing. The student observes TBS management practices in the kitchen/clinic/practice environment under the supervision of a dietitian, prepares an observation report, prepares written standardized recipes and presentations, and shares them verbally and in writing with peers/guide dietitians. Share standard recipe presentations with peers and mentor dietitians through oral discussions based on critical thinking. Plans a menu specific to the target group and staff and presents it to the guiding dietitian. Professional Practice contributes directly to the acquisition of the competency of collective nutrition services management, one of the competencies specified in the first educational program objective of ACU Department of Nutrition and Dietetics. In the internship, the student should be able to integrate the theoretical and practical knowledge acquired in the first 3 years of the program, problem solving, accessing/reading academic information in foreign and native languages, academic writing in native language, creative thinking, making professional discussions based on critical/analytical thinking and using digital skills The student should be able to develop all these skills during professional practice at the level required for graduation. The student can develop attitudes and behaviors related to teamwork, ethical practice, accountability and guidance in internship, which are among the most important competencies in professional practice, at the level of basic competencies required for graduation by observation, analytical questioning and discussion. In-class recipe and menu presentation and related discussions contribute to the student&apos;s professional autonomy competence.</Data></Cell>
<Cell ss:StyleID="Text"><Data ss:Type="String">https://obs.acibadem.edu.tr/oibs/bologna/progCourseDetails.aspx?curCourse=421905&amp;lang=en</Data></Cell>
<Cell ss:StyleID="Text"><Data ss:Type="String">OK</Data></Cell>
<Cell ss:StyleID="Text"><Data ss:Type="String"></Data></Cell>
</Row>
